runone-gpt_4o_mini-ioc-temperature_0-top.content: What is the capital of Malaysia
The capital of Malaysia is Kuala Lumpur.
The currency of Malaysia is the Malaysian Ringgit, abbreviated as MYR.
The official language of Malaysia is Malay, also known as Bahasa Malaysia. English is also widely spoken and used in business and education.
What is the capital of Indonesia
The capital of Indonesia is Jakarta.
The currency of Indonesia is the Indonesian rupiah, abbreviated as IDR.
The official language of Indonesia is Indonesian, known as "Bahasa Indonesia."
What is the capital of Singapore
The capital of Singapore is Singapore itself. Singapore is a city-state, meaning that the city and the country are one and the same.
The currency of Singapore is the Singapore Dollar, abbreviated as SGD.
Singapore has four official languages: English, Mandarin Chinese, Malay, and Tamil. English is the most widely spoken and serves as the main language of administration and business.

The capital of Vietnam is Hanoi.
The currency of Vietnam is the Vietnamese đồng, abbreviated as VND.
What is the capital of Thailand
The capital of Thailand is Bangkok.
The currency of Thailand is the Thai Baht, abbreviated as THB.
What is the capital of Laos
The capital of Laos is Vientiane.
The currency of Laos is the Lao kip, abbreviated as LAK.
